text.tspan: FIGURE 3 top left, top right and bottom left compare distribution densities at the centre of the distribution.
The Laplace, horseshoe and horseshoe+ distributions place increasingly large probability volume close to the
central value, promoting sparsity in estimated parameter sets. Bottom right compares density in the tail of the
distribution. The Gaussian tail is not displayed as it is not distinguishable from zero on the plotted scale.
